4 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
5 SECTION 1. AMENDMENT. Section 54-03-02 of the North Dakota Century Code is
6 amended and reenacted as follows:
7 54-03-02. When legislative assembly meets.
8 1. The legislative assembly shall meet at the seat of government in the month of
9 December following the election of theits members thereof for organizational and
10 orientation purposes and shall thereafter recess until the time provided in
11 subsection 2.
12 2. The legislative assembly shall reconvene at twelve noonannually for a number of days
13 to be determined by the legislative assembly, but the number of days must be
14 scheduled within a seventy calendar day period each year, subject to subsection 3 .
15 a. Each year, the legislative assembly shall convene on the first TuesdayMonday
16 after the third day in January of the year following the organizational session as
17 provided in subsection 1 or at twelve noon on a date selected by the legislative
18 management but not earlier than January second nor later than January eleventh
19 of the year following the organizational session and, following. At the close of
20 business of the regular session, the legislative assembly shall adjournrecess
21 subject to subsection 3.
22 b. The first week of each year the legislative assembly is convened, it shall convene
23 on Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday, and Friday. Thereafter, the
24 legislative assembly shall primarily convene on Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday,
